PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.NOME-DO-PROJETO: Estudo dos eventos dos ciclos cardнacos em sedentбrios de ambos os sexos
PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.DESCRICAO-DO-PROJETO: Physical activities ? walking, fitness and ballroom dancing - were offered over a six month period (April-September 2007). Sixty-minute classes were offered three times a week, in the morning, at the Physical Activities Stand, in a program called Mexa-se (Move your Body). Each class was divided into three stages: warm-up (10 minutes); the class itself (45 minutes); and stretching and relaxation exercises performed to background music, in the last phase (05 minutes). Twenty-five sedentary individuals took part in this study: n=09 men (ages 34 to 50) and n=16 women (ages 31 to 51). This study aims to verify the effects of the program on the following cardiac cycle events: Systolic Blood Pressure (SBP), Diastolic Blood Pressure (DBP) and heart rate (HR). The Naughton Protocol was applied and the individuals were evaluated and re-evaluated according to the aforesaid methodology. Heart rate, Systolic Blood Pressure and Diastolic Blood Pressure at rest and during post-exercise recovery were statistically analyzed t-test, with p>0.05 significance level. At rest: in both sexes, there was no significant difference between evaluation and re-evaluation heart rate; regarding SBP and DBP, only the men showed a significant difference between evaluation and re-evaluation values. At recovery: there was no difference between evaluation and re-evaluation heart rate in either group (men and women); SBP was different between evaluation and re-evaluation in both groups from the first minute up to the sixth minute; regarding DBP, there was no difference in the first minute, but from the second minute onward, both groups showed a difference between evaluation and re-evaluation values. It should also be noted that at evaluation, both groups completed the Protocol to the 4th stage, and at re-evaluation, 37.5% of females and 33.3% of males completed the Protocol to the 5th and 6th stages. For statistical analysis, we only included up to the 4th stage in the re-evaluation, which showed a significant difference for the male group but not for the female group. Through these results, we observed that the offered physical activity program was an efficient means to a cardiac cycle events.

PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.DESCRICAO-DO-PROJETO: RESUMO Das patologias nutricionais a obesidade й que mais tem apresentado aumento em seus nъmeros, nгo apenas nos paнses ricos, mas tambйm nos paнses em desenvolvimento. O excesso de peso, segundo Pollock e Wilmore (1993), ?й definido como aquela condiзгo onde o peso do indivнduo excede ao da mйdia da populaзгo, determinada segundo o sexo, a altura e o tipo de compleiзгo fнsica?, sendo a obesidade caracterizada como ?um excesso de gordura corporal?. Serгo estudados escolares de ambos os sexos, pertencentes as escolas estaduais e municipais da cidade de Trкs Lagoas-MS. DADOS-BASICOS-DO-TRABALHO.TITULO-DO-TRABALHO: Effect of the acute carbohydrate ingestion on performance in high-intensity continuous aerobic exercice

DETALHAMENTO-DO-TRABALHO.NOME-DO-EVENTO: 8th Annual Congress of European College of Sport Science
DETALHAMENTO-DO-TRABALHO.TITULO-DOS-ANAIS-OU-PROCEEDINGS: 8th Annual Congress of European College of Sport Science

INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS.DESCRICAO-INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS: The purpose of this study was to investigate the effect of the acute ingestion of CHO on performance in high-intensity and short duration continuous aerobic exercise. Six amateur male cyclists (28.7 9.3 years; body mass 66.3 4.1 kg; height 170.0 6.3 cm; VO2max 57.0 5.0 ml.kg-1.min-1) performed continuous test at 80% of load in maximum oxygen consumption (Wvo2max) in two different situations, after fractionate ingestion of carbohydrate (CHO) or placebo (PL), administrated in a rate of 0.5 g.kg-1 at 60, 45 and 30 minutes before the beginning of each test. The subjects performed tests with an interval of 72 h between each test, randomized and double-blinded. Blood samples were collected immediately before and after effort for glucose, insulin, cortisol and lactate determination. Exhaustion time at CHO condition was significantly lower than PL condition (15.5 1.9 vs 16.8 2.2 min, P<0.01). No differences were observed in VO2, VE, HR in comparison to CHO and PL conditions (P>0.05). Significant differences were observed in pre and post-effort at respiratory coefficient (R) with elevated values at CHO condition (P<0.001). Pre-exercise blood glucose was significantly higher at CHO condition than PL (8.2 1.0 vs 4.9 0.7 mmol.l-1, p<0.001), as well as insulin levels (44.6 7.4 vs 12.7 9.2 mU/ml, P<0.01). Blood lactate and plasmatic cortisol didn't show any significant alterations in the comparison between the treatments (P>0.05). The ingestion of CHO (1.5 g.kg-1 fractionated at 60, 45, and 30 minutes) before exercise, resulted in reduction of 8% in physical performance. Besides, it provided an increase in glucose and insulin blood levels. We believe that the stimulated hyperinsulinemia for increase of circulating glucose may have contributed to the decrease in physical performance. We suggest that the ingestion of CHO before the beginning of the test seemed to lower the performance in high-intensity and short duration continuos aerobic exercise

DADOS-BASICOS-DO-TRABALHO.TITULO-DO-TRABALHO: Does Critical Swimming velocity exercice intensity at maximal lactate steady state in adolescent swimmers?

DETALHAMENTO-DO-TRABALHO.NOME-DO-EVENTO: 8th Annual Congress of the European College of Sport Science, 2003. p. 267.
DETALHAMENTO-DO-TRABALHO.TITULO-DOS-ANAIS-OU-PROCEEDINGS: 8th Annual Congress of the European College of Sport Science, 2003. p. 267.

INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS.DESCRICAO-INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS: The purpose of this study is to investigate if critical velocity (CV) effectively corresponds to Maximal Lactate Steady State (MLSS) in adolescent swimmers. Six male swimmers (15.2 0.4 years) were submitted to swim three different distances (50, 100 and 200 m) crawl style at maximal effort in random order. The CV was defined by the inclination of the linear regression line between distances and their respective times obtained each repetition. For the definition of MLSS, the subject performed three tests (5 x 200 m) with a 24 h interval in randomized order in the velocities corresponding to 98%, 100% and 102% of CV, with a 30 second pause between the 200 m for collection of blood and lactate analyses at the end of the first, third and fifth 200 m. In the intensity corresponding to 98% of CV a difference between the lactate concentrations was found between the first and the third 200 m (1.95 0.51 vs 2.62 1.07 mmol.l-1; P<0.05), but no difference was found between the third and fifth 200 m (2.62 1.07 vs 2.65 0.99 mmol.l-1; P<0.05). For the intensities of 100% and 102% a difference in lactate between the first and the third, and a difference in lactate between the third and fifth 200 m (P<0.05) were found. The lactate concentration in the first, third and fifth 200 m was greater in the intensities of 100% and 102% than in the 200 m corresponding to 98% of CV (P<0.05). Accordingly, the lactate concentration in the intensity corresponding to 102% of CV was greater in the first, third and fifth 200 m than in the intensity of 100% of CV (P<0.05). A decrease in the blood lactate concentration was observed from the third 200 m in the intensities of 100% and 102% of CV, which occurred due to the non maintenance of swimming velocity by the subjects. Thus, the CV seems to overestimate MLSS in adolescent swimmers, what may have important implications in the evaluation and prescription of training in children. .

DADOS-BASICOS-DO-TRABALHO.TITULO-DO-TRABALHO: Effects of creatine Supplementation on Aerobic Performance in Wingate Test

DETALHAMENTO-DO-TRABALHO.NOME-DO-EVENTO: Annual Congress of the European College of Sport Science, 2003,
DETALHAMENTO-DO-TRABALHO.TITULO-DOS-ANAIS-OU-PROCEEDINGS: Annual Congress of the European College of Sport Science, 2003,

INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS.DESCRICAO-INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS: The purpose of this study was to verify the effects of 5 days of creatine supplementation on performance in the Wingate Test. The sample was composed by 22 healthy individuals (23.5 2.9 years) involved in a weight training program. The subjects were supplemented with creatine (CR; n= 11; body mass 77.6 11.8 kg; height 181.0 6.8 cm; BMI 23.7 3.7 kg/m2) or placebo (maltodextrin) (PL; n= 11; body mass 74.7 10.4 kg; height 177.0 9.2 cm; BMI 23.8 2.3 kg/m2) during 5 days (4 doses of 5.2 g = 20.8 g/day), using a double blind procedure. The Wingate Test was used to evaluate anaerobic performance, adopting load corresponding to 9 g.kg-1 of the subject's body mass. The Wingate Test was applied one day before the beginning of the supplementation and 6 days after the beginning of the supplementation. The analysis performance indexes were relative peak power (RPP) and relative mean power (RMP). For statistical treatment of RPP and RMP the repeated measures analysis of covariance (ANCOVA) and the repeated measures analysis of variance (ANOVA) were used, respectively. When differences by ANOVA or ANCOVA were found the Tukey post hoc test was employed (P<0.05). After supplementation the CR group increased its performance in RMP (8.9 0.7 vs 9.3 0.7; P<0.05) with no changes in RPP (12.2 0.8 vs 12.7 0.9; P>0.05). On the other hand, the PL group did not present changes in either of the analyzed indexes (RPP - 11.6 0.9 vs 11.8 0.9; RMP - 8.9 0.5 vs 8.8 0.4; P>0.05). From the results we may conclude that creatine supplementation has demonstrated to be an efficient ergogenic resource in activities of high-intensity and short duration, and mainly in the capacity of supporting this effort. .

INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS.DESCRICAO-INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS: A condiзгo em que a reabsorзгo уssea excede os depуsitos уsseos acarreta numa diminuiзгo na massa mineral do osso, resultando em densidade mineral уssea reduzida (perda de dureza do osso e perda de integridade trabecular). Em adultos jovens, os depуsitos уsseos ocorrem na mesma proporзгo que a reabsorзгo уssea, e a massa уssea total й relativamente constante. Entretanto, um estilo de vida saudбvel parece ser fundamental na manutenзгo da saъde уssea. Nesse sentido, o exercнcio fнsico й um componente importante para o desenvolvimento e manutenзгo do sistema esquelйtico. Diante desses fatos, o objetivo de presente estudo foi estabelecer comparaзхes entre os depуsitos уsseos em adultos jovens envolvidos em treinamento com pesos e sedentбrios. A amostra foi constituнda por 23 indivнduos que foram subdivididos em grupo treinamento (GT; n=12) e grupo sedentбrio (GS; n=11). Mediante aplicaзгo do mйtodo de absortometria de raio-X de dupla energia (DEXA) foram comparadas as seguintes variбveis: gordura relativa (GR), massa isenta de gordura (MIG), massa isenta de osso (MIO), massa de gordura (MG), conteъdo mineral уsseo (CMO) e densidade mineral уssea (DMO). O teste t de Student nгo revelou diferenзas significantes entre os grupos nos componentes de gordura (MG) e mъsculo (MIG e MIO). Entretanto, o GT apresentou valores estatisticamente mais elevados de CMO (10%) e DMO (7%) do que o GS. De acordo com estes resultados, pode-se concluir que o treinamento com pesos, por proporcionar estresses mecвnicos aos ossos, parece contribuir para aumento nos depуsitos уsseos. Um desenvolvimento уsseo adequado nesta fase minimiza os efeitos do processo de perda da massa уssea com o avanзar da idade..
